   <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-11294">
  	

     <div id="comment-11294" >
	 
	 <div class="comment-metaLeft">
			<img src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a0512fab1202478d890d889d1c24839d?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2F61a58ec1c1fba116f8424035089b7c71%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G' alt='' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />			</div>
			<div class="commentRight">
			<div class="commentBullet"></div>
				 <span><strong>Jay</strong> </span>February 18, 2011 at 15:44 				
				  <div class="text"><p>Good knowledge base. Had a question with recursive copy, -r option. It appears that you need to create the directory structure at your destination node before issuing an scp with -r option. I tried to copy without creating the nested directory structure (it is quite complex) in my destination node and it came up with an error, 'Is a Directory'. Can you clarify if this is an scp limitation or I am missing something. Thanks</p>
 </div>
				   			<div class="reply">
					 <a class='comment-reply-link' href='http://www.linuxtutorialblog.com/post/ssh-and-scp-howto-tips-tricks?replytocom=11294#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-11294", "11294", "respond", "1")'>Reply</a>				  </div>
