				  <div class="text"><p>Above is a good article and I learnt from it and below is a specific scenario that was missing from the article.<br />
Please find the below syntax.<br />
if you want to transfer file from your local to remote machine where your local is windows OS and your remote is UNIX ...and the port is not default 22 then user the below command<br />
scp -P     @:/home//</p>
<p>scp -P 9378 myfile <a href="mailto:samay@172.19.235.40">samay@172.19.235.40</a>:/home/samay/myfile</p>
