     <div id="comment-84908" >
	 
	 <div class="comment-metaLeft">
			<img src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/841d461f2528ab5b584954869f80136a?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2F61a58ec1c1fba116f8424035089b7c71%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G' alt='' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />			</div>
			<div class="commentRight">
			<div class="commentBullet"></div>
				 <span><strong><a href='2007/01' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>rechosen</a></strong> </span>April 12, 2012 at 14:52 				
				  <div class="text"><p>I actually meant that I'd show later how to connect <em>with</em> specifying a username, but it's easily misread :). That said, you can connect without specifying a username if you either (1) connect to a host that takes the username you're logged in as right now, or (2) by configuring a username in your ssh config (see man ssh_config).</p>
 </div>
