				 <span><strong><a href='2007/01' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>rechosen</a></strong> </span>April 12, 2012 at 14:58 				
				  <div class="text"><p>To specify a port, use the -p option in ssh or the -P option in scp. The :<something> syntax is reserved for specifying the file/dir to copy using scp.</something></p>
 </div>
				   			<div class="reply">
					 <a class='comment-reply-link' href='http://www.linuxtutorialblog.com/post/ssh-and-scp-howto-tips-tricks?replytocom=84911#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-84911", "84911", "respond", "1")'>Reply</a>				  </div>
